rrative means (military descriptions, presentation of peoples, march-narratives, anachronies, and epic elements) in order to draw the reader’s attention not only to Alexander’s intellectual skills but also to the fact that the king was gradually corrupted by his success. This book puts Arrian’s literary contrivances under the microscope, sheds new light on unexplored aspects of the Anabasis’ narrative arrangement, and contributes to the studies of Alexander’s prosopography in Classical historiography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAlexander der Große. 4aArrian. 4aMazedonien. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAlexander the Great.  aAlexandrou Anabasis.  aArrian.  aMacedonia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishz978311061685908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishz978311061009308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019z9783110605945oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831106587980 cprintz978311065873640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311065997940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110659979423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110659979.jpg  a978-3-11-061009-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061685-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE  DG 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EB